{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/background-information/prognosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"7b16d20a-13e6-5b29-b45a-00e4f7e8dc88","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 9d0b305a-d022-40f8-8260-d6928b4f98ec --><h2>What is the prognosis?</h2><!-- end field 9d0b305a-d022-40f8-8260-d6928b4f98ec -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 71268975-c9e1-474a-b229-925e587c1ce2 --><!-- begin field e5936fc3-4754-489c-94d8-714bdf5a8417 --><ul><li><strong>Travellers' diarrhoea is, for most people, a short-lived, self-limiting illness with recovery in a few days </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">WHO, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>]. It is rarely life-threatening [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett, 2016</a>].  <ul><li>The severity of travellers' diarrhoea depends on the cause and the individual person [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">NaTHNaC, 2016</a>]. Most people do not have severe enough symptoms to be confined to bed or need medical attention [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett and Brown, 2018</a>]. </li><li>The effects of travellers' diarrhoea are greater in very young children, elderly people and people living with frailty [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">NaTHNaC, 2016</a>]. </li></ul></li><li>In terms of duration:<ul><li>Most episodes last up to seven days [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett, 2016</a>], with 8 out of 10 episodes resolving within a week [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett and Brown, 2018</a>]. </li><li>It is thought that [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>]: <ul><li>Untreated bacterial diarrhoea lasts around 3–7 days.</li><li>Viral diarrhoea lasts around 2–3 days.</li></ul></li><li>About 10% of episodes last for longer than 1 week, 5% persist for longer than 2 weeks, and 1% have a duration of more than 30 days [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Barrett, 2016</a>]. <ul><li>Prolonged diarrhoeal symptoms are more likely if the person is immunocompromised or has a protozoal infection. Protozoal diarrhoea can persist for weeks to months without treatment [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>]. <strong> </strong></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field e5936fc3-4754-489c-94d8-714bdf5a8417 --><!-- end item 71268975-c9e1-474a-b229-925e587c1ce2 -->","topic":{"id":"d5cf1db6-a6d9-54fb-b393-095d8af57067","topicId":"9042b194-f66e-44c6-a91c-76ffa626e3e8","topicName":"Diarrhoea - prevention and advice for travellers","slug":"diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2019","chapters":[{"id":"3f7bee04-88e6-5a40-86d5-e39dc29e4059","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47ddb819-f046-5e92-999c-a3d47a00ede8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bdd3d81e-da2b-5807-b257-8dd4d73a596c","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5ac4ad9d-b3fb-51c6-84de-19181b30e02c","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5568a30c-164d-5d4f-8d41-ad7eff1173cb","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6f04e901-40c5-5906-a7eb-5935a99758bb","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e0f32109-cb0a-51e3-aa59-bcac4a364a5f","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a74f052-b6c8-5743-b69f-30ffc630174e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"81c43095-b29a-537e-ad23-56ca74d2e6fb","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"6e2e9744-c361-5fb3-91e7-f843ad784aec","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"09edec10-2e6b-5f71-a4d8-df80e8029f64","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"6079457e-dedc-595c-98b9-9e1d2968d8e5","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"5b021b39-4f64-5d7c-ac92-3e6fcb9ca47e","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"bbb9e2c5-c538-5f62-a833-9b160d36c0bf","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"3a92beb8-79d6-5dae-ab0f-e43917551a50","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"862305f2-71ed-541b-b207-349e412f7b36","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"e8fd2377-deba-5e27-9879-c44fb6974ce6","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"6b06fe10-6c53-5fef-a9b5-481286e08753","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"7b16d20a-13e6-5b29-b45a-00e4f7e8dc88","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"b22ec23d-37e6-515d-9c3f-e1ca62a98b3d","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"b6fabe34-4002-50c9-bd67-e106a239ca67","s